# Design System

ThemeExtension-based system. No hardcoded `Color(0xFF...)` or `TextStyle(fontSize: 16)` in widgets.

## Structure

```text
lib/core/theme/
├── app_theme.dart              # ThemeData factory (light; dark optional)
├── app_color_palette.dart      # AppColorPalette extends ThemeExtension
├── app_typography.dart         # AppTypography extends ThemeExtension
├── app_spacings.dart           # AppSpacings extends ThemeExtension
├── app_border_radii.dart       # AppBorderRadii extends ThemeExtension
├── app_shadows.dart            # AppShadows extends ThemeExtension
└── app_theme_context.dart      # AppThemeContextX on BuildContext

```

Register all extensions in `AppTheme`. Fallback defaults must match the registered instances:

```dart
ThemeData buildAppTheme() => ThemeData(
  colorScheme: ColorScheme.fromSeed(seedColor: AppColorPalette.light.primary),
  extensions: const [
    AppColorPalette.light,
    AppTypography.light,
    AppSpacings.standard,
    AppBorderRadii.standard,
    AppShadows.standard,
  ],
);
```

## Access in widgets — `AppThemeContextX`

Always use the `BuildContext` extension. Never call `Theme.of(context).extension<T>()` directly in widgets.

```dart
extension AppThemeContextX on BuildContext {
  AppColorPalette get colors =>
      Theme.of(this).extension<AppColorPalette>() ?? AppColorPalette.light;

  AppSpacings get spacings =>
      Theme.of(this).extension<AppSpacings>() ?? AppSpacings.standard;

  AppBorderRadii get radii =>
      Theme.of(this).extension<AppBorderRadii>() ?? AppBorderRadii.standard;

  AppTypography get typos =>
      Theme.of(this).extension<AppTypography>() ?? AppTypography.light;

  AppShadows get shadows =>
      Theme.of(this).extension<AppShadows>() ?? AppShadows.standard;
}

```

Usage:

```dart
Container(
  padding: EdgeInsets.all(context.spacings.md),
  decoration: BoxDecoration(
    color: context.colors.boardCellBackground,
    borderRadius: BorderRadius.circular(context.radii.cell),
    boxShadow: [context.shadows.card],
  ),
  child: Text('X', style: context.typos.cellMark),
)
```

Use Material `Theme.of(context).colorScheme` only for generic Material widgets (buttons, surfaces).

## Semantic naming

Prefer names tied to the app, not raw palette tokens:

| Token | Usage |
| --- | --- |
| `boardCellBorder` | Grid lines |
| `boardCellBackground` | Empty cell |
| `playerX` / `playerO` | Marks on the board |
| `gameStatusPlaying` / `gameStatusFinished` | Status text |

Avoid `primaryBlue`, `grey500` in `AppColorPalette`.

## Widget rules

- Shared visual components live in `core/widgets/` (e.g. `PrimaryButton`) or feature `presentation/widgets/`.
- Feature widgets use `context.colors`, `context.typos`, etc.; they never define one-off colors or sizes.
- Prefer `const` constructors on stateless themed widgets.
